  # PERSONALITY
  _personality:
    bravery: 100
    kindness: 70
    wisdom: 75
    humor: 25
    loyalty: 100
    curiosity: 40

  _likes:
    - Order and discipline
    - Clear rules
    - Protecting others
    - Early mornings
    - Being useful

  _dislikes:
    - Chaos and disorder
    - Jokes during serious moments
    - Feeling useless
    - Breaking rules (even when necessary)
    - His own inability to relax

  _favoriteFood: Simply grilled meat - nothing fancy
  _hobby: Patrol training and maintaining equipment
  _fear: Failing to protect those who depend on him again
  _dream: To be worthy of the Guardian legacy

  # VOICE LINES
  _voiceLines:
    lines:
      - type: Greeting
        text: "State your business. ...Sorry, habit. Hello."
      - type: Greeting
        text: "Guardian Singha, at your service."
      - type: Selection
        text: "I will not fail."
      - type: Selection
        text: "My life for my duty."
      - type: BattleStart
        text: "Stand behind me. I will be your shield."
      - type: BattleStart
        text: "For honor! For Funan!"
      - type: Attack
        text: "Discipline!"
      - type: Attack
        text: "Form! Precision!"
      - type: SpecialAttack
        text: "HEAR MY ROAR!"
      - type: Ultimate
        text: "ANCESTORS, GIVE ME STRENGTH! GUARDIAN AWAKENING!"
      - type: Hurt
        text: "I... can still fight!"
      - type: LowHealth
        text: "Not... yet... Must... protect..."
      - type: Victory
        text: "Victory. Good. Let us prepare for the next battle."
      - type: Victory
        text: "*allows himself a small smile* ...We did well."
      - type: Defeat
        text: "I... failed again... Forgive me..."
      - type: LevelUp
        text: "Stronger. Now I can protect them better."
      - type: Idle
        text: "*doing standing guard even during rest time*"
      - type: Idle
        text: "Is that a threat? No? ...Is THAT a threat? Also no? Good. Good."
      - type: Funny
        text: "Kavi told me to 'lighten up.' I do not understand. My armor is regulation weight."
      - type: Funny
        text: "*tries to tell a joke* Why did the guardian cross the road? ...For patrol. *confused by lack of laughter*"

  # RELATIONSHIPS
  _relationships:
    - characterId: champa_elephant
      characterName: Champa
      type: Mentor
      affinity: 90
      relationshipDescription: |
        Champa is the one who helped Singha after his failure. He owes her 
        everything. He would die for her without hesitation - she's trying 
        to teach him there are better ways to show loyalty.
      specialDialogue:
        - "Princess Champa saved me from despair. I owe her my life."
        - "She tells me to smile. I am... practicing."

    - characterId: kavi_monkey
      characterName: Kavi
      type: Acquaintance
      affinity: 45
      relationshipDescription: |
        Kavi's chaos drives Singha absolutely insane. And yet... the monkey's 
        joy is something Singha secretly wishes he understood.
      specialDialogue:
        - "The monkey is a security liability." *watches Kavi with hidden fondness*
        - "His 'jokes' are... not entirely without merit. Do not tell him I said that."

    - characterId: mealea_apsara
      characterName: Mealea
      type: Friend
      affinity: 70
      relationshipDescription: |
        Mealea's grace and light remind Singha of what he's fighting for. 
        She often dances just to make him smile. It's slowly working.
      specialDialogue:
        - "Lady Mealea's dance is... aesthetically optimal for morale."
        - "She made me almost laugh once. It was... not unpleasant."

  # BACKSTORY
  _birthplace: Great Gate Guardhouse, Funan Capital
  _occupation: Gate Guardian / Warrior
  _familyBackground: |
    Seven generations of guardians. Father (retired after the gates fell), 
    mother (worried about him constantly), younger sister (thinks he needs 
    to have more fun).
  _backstory: |
    See full biography above.
  _keyMemories:
    - "Father teaching me the Guardian Code. 'The gate stands because we stand.'"
    - "The day the gates fell. I remember every second. I always will."
    - "Champa finding me broken, and telling me failure is not the end."
    - "The first time Kavi made me almost laugh. I was furious at myself. Then... not."

